<item>
            <title>[HIVE-10571] HiveMetaStoreClient should close existing thrift connection before its reconnect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-10571</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;HiveMetaStoreClient should first close its existing thrift connection, no matter it is already dead or still live, before its opening another connection in its reconnect() method. Otherwise, it might lead to resource huge accumulation or leak at HMS site when client keeps on retrying.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
